WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:39.600
 The baby is still too small. Another 
 few weeks would make the difference. 

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:41.680
 That'll be the case, please God. 

00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:45.720
 I'm not even 30 weeks gone. 
 The baby won't stand a chance. 

00:00:45.800 --> 00:00:47.800
 Don't talk like that, Suzy. 

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:50.600
 With the help of God, 
 that mightn't even happen. 

00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:53.280
 With the help of God, 
 it mightn't happen? 

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:55.960
 Thanks a bunch. 
 What a consolation that is! 

00:00:56.040 --> 00:00:58.040
 Everything will be alright, Suzy. 

00:00:58.120 --> 00:01:01.360
 Either way, 
 you'll be well looked after. 

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:04.280
 -Suzy Loughlin? 
 -Declan Brosnan. Hello Ríona. 

00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:05.400
 Hi! 

00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:09.480
 -I'd like a word with you. 
 -Stay here Ríona. 

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:11.560
 Okay, if that's what you want. 

00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:13.640
 You have a great friend there! 

00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:17.920
 We're very proud of Ríona. 
 She's one of the best trainee nurses.

00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:21.080
 Okay, this is how it is. 

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:24.080
 I spoke to the doctors 
 in orthopaedics. 

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:27.680
 There's a strong possibility 
 that your cheekbone is broken. 

00:01:27.760 --> 00:01:30.600
 Another doctor will discuss that 
 with you later. 

00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:33.880
 My biggest concern 
 is the bleeding from the womb. 

00:01:33.960 --> 00:01:35.760
 What caused it? 

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:37.880
 A condition called placenta praevia.

00:01:37.960 --> 00:01:42.960
 It means that the connection between 
 the placenta and the womb is weak. 

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:47.120
 If it worsens, we'll have 
 to carry out an emergency Caesarean.

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:49.200
 -Caesarean? 
 -Don't worry. 

00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:52.080
 We have a very experienced team. 

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:54.240
 I don't want a Caesarean. 

00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:57.920
 It'll only happen 
 in the case of an emergency. 

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.800
 Whatever happens, 
 I don't want an operation. 

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:05.040
 I'm sorry but if you start to bleed 
 again, there'll be no alternative. 

00:02:05.120 --> 00:02:08.520
 They'll give you an anaesthetic. 
 You won't feel a thing. 

00:02:08.600 --> 00:02:10.840
 -General anaesthetic? 
 -Yes. 

00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:15.800
 No, you have to keep the baby 
 inside. I don't want an operation. 

00:02:15.880 --> 00:02:18.600
 That's what we're trying to avoid. 

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:22.680
 However, you must understand that 
 sometimes there's no alternative. 

00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:26.480
 -What have I done now? 
 -That was HQ on the phone. 

00:02:26.560 --> 00:02:29.560
 They're sending an inspector 
 to Ros na Rún. 

00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:32.520
 They finally copped on 
 that you're useless! 

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:37.640
 They're investigating 
 the previous sergeant actually. 

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:40.720
 This is all very interesting 
 but I'm on my way home. 

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:44.680
 Look it! I don't want any trouble 
 while the inspector is around. 

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:47.080
 Stay well away from Daniel McLoughlin

00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:49.600
 I had no intention of going near him.

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:51.160
 Good. 

00:02:51.240 --> 00:02:55.280
 Don't draw any attention to yourself
 and everything will be fine. 

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.800
 What has this got to do with me? 

00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:02.520
 This is my first job as sergeant 
 and it's on a trial basis. 

00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:06.280
 If my brother goes around causing 
 trouble, it'll go against me. 

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:10.040
 What are you doing here? 

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:12.120
 I told you I didn't want to see you.

00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:15.320
 How could I not come to see you? 
 Are you alright? 

00:03:15.400 --> 00:03:18.600
 -Do I have to call the nurse? 
 -What about the baby? 

00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:20.880
 Please Suzy, just two minutes. 

00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:26.480
 Look, I know you're fuming with me. 

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:30.920
 You must believe me when I say that 
 I didn't know you'd be in danger. 

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:33.200
 I'm serious. 

00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:36.440
 Had I known it'd be risky, 
 I wouldn't have sent you. 

00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:39.640
 This is all your fault 
 at the end of the day. 

00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:43.240
 Don't say that! Can't you see 
 how much this upsets me? 

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:47.280
 I went around to the brothel 
 last night to kill that bastard. 

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:49.560
 There was no one there of course. 

00:03:49.640 --> 00:03:52.360
 I guess he was afraid 
 I'd go to the police. 

00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:56.200
 Why didn't you say it was a brothel, 
 when we were on the phone? 

00:03:56.280 --> 00:03:58.360
 He told me it was an office. 

00:03:58.440 --> 00:04:02.120
 There was an office alright 
 and plenty of bedrooms too! 

00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:04.280
 God Almighty! 

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:06.400
 I'm so sorry. 

00:04:07.800 --> 00:04:10.960
 I can't understand 
 why it's bothering me so much. 

00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:13.200
 It shouldn't bother you at all. 

00:04:13.280 --> 00:04:15.840
 You did nothing wrong. 

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:19.720
 They just couldn't take Oscar 
 from his family. 

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:22.240
 I know that, Peadar. 

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:26.480
 It'd be nice to mind him, 
 just the two of us. 

00:04:26.560 --> 00:04:28.520
 I'm so fond of him. 

00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:32.200
 I know that, Máire, but 
 you do take care of him every day. 

00:04:32.280 --> 00:04:34.360
 And great care at that. 

00:04:34.440 --> 00:04:39.160
 It's only natural to bring him 
 to see his mother at the weekend. 

00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:43.120
 There's nothing more 
 you can do for him. 

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:45.320
 Even they themselves said that. 

00:04:45.400 --> 00:04:48.800
 At least this way 
 we can get a night's sleep. 

00:04:48.880 --> 00:04:50.960
 I know, Peadar. 

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:56.920
 It's just that I had my heart set 
 on fostering Oscar this time around.

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:01.200
 That's not how it works, love. 

00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.480
 We should count ourselves lucky. 

00:05:03.560 --> 00:05:06.960
 You mind Oscar every day 
 and Evan is only next door. 

00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:10.640
 Not every old couple are that lucky 
 in this day and age. 

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:12.960
 You're right. We are lucky. 

00:05:13.400 --> 00:05:15.200
 Máire. 

00:05:16.560 --> 00:05:20.280
 I think you should have a chat 
 with Berni about this. 

00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:24.520
 She thinks she's to blame 
 that we didn't get Oscar. 

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.080
 I'll talk to her, don't worry. 

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:30.840
 I'm very proud of you. 

00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:32.640
 Why? 

00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:34.680
 Why wouldn't I be? 

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:37.960
 It's great to see yourself and Berni
 getting on again. 

00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:40.720
 You're setting Evan a great example.

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:43.760
 Seeing his mother and grandmother 
 getting along. 

00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:46.000
 Let's go! 

00:05:46.920 --> 00:05:49.760
 Are you going to report him 
 to the Gardaí? 

00:05:49.840 --> 00:05:52.240
 That would suit you, wouldn't it? 

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:55.600
 That way, you wouldn't be suspected.

00:05:55.680 --> 00:05:57.600
 Stop that nonsense! 

00:05:57.680 --> 00:05:59.800
 It's not nonsense. 

00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:02.120
 You'll pay for what you did to me. 

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:05.400
 You're not using your head, Suzy. 

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:11.000
 Both of us need to think of a way 
 to get even with that bastard. 

00:06:11.080 --> 00:06:13.400
 But we need to go about it carefully.

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:17.880
 Let bygones be bygones. We have 
 to pull together, this is no joke. 

00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:20.400
 Who are you telling? 

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:22.520
 Right! 

00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:27.080
 I wouldn't recommend 
 involving the Gardaí yet. 

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:29.840
 We're dealing with a dangerous man. 

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:33.480
 I know exactly 
 what kind of a man he is. 

00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:35.440
 Hello. 

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.880
 Are you busy? 

00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:40.120
 Someone's got to do it. 

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:44.920
 I could be here until kingdom come 
 waiting for them to lift a finger! 

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.600
 They can't be that bad. 

00:06:47.680 --> 00:06:50.560
 The youth of today don't know 
 the meaning of work. 

00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:54.960
 Youth? Those two aren't in the prime
 of their youth anymore. 

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:57.040
 What are you talking about? 

00:06:57.120 --> 00:06:59.520
 I'm twice as old as the two of them.

00:06:59.600 --> 00:07:04.400
 And I've done three times as much 
 work as the two of them put together.

00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:07.320
 They can go to hell for all I care! 

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:10.920
 The Lord save us and bless us! 

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.960
 I'm fine, Peadar. 

00:07:13.040 --> 00:07:14.600
 Gosh! 

00:07:14.680 --> 00:07:16.680
 Are you alright, Séamus? 

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:18.560
 You did a little somersault there! 

00:07:18.640 --> 00:07:23.240
 You should stop drinking at lunch 
 time! You're not a young lad anymore.

00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:25.760
 Frig off you wasters! 

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:28.480
 Is that your equipment? 

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:30.760
 Is that your equipment? 

00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:33.680
 Yes, Sergeant. 

00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:37.320
 Put it in a safe place. 
 It's causing a hazard there. 

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:39.320
 I'm sorry, Sergeant. 

00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:43.120
 We're working on the car. 
 Only for that, it wouldn't be there.

00:07:43.200 --> 00:07:45.560
 It tripped Séamus. 

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:49.280
 Never mind, Séamus. 
 Séamus is just fine. 

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:53.000
 He wasn't hurt. There's no point 
 making a big deal about it. 

00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:56.360
 It'll be a big deal 
 if it happens again. 

00:07:56.440 --> 00:08:01.960
 Now if you don't mind, 
 put that equipment in a safe place. 

00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:04.680
 And don't let it happen again. 

00:08:04.760 --> 00:08:06.640
 Okay, Sergeant. 

00:08:10.400 --> 00:08:15.600
 Maybe I can't get my revenge 
 on that bastard for what he did... 

00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:19.640
 ..but as for you, 
 that's quite another matter. 

00:08:19.720 --> 00:08:23.000
 What good will that do you, Suzy? 

00:08:23.080 --> 00:08:26.440
 To see you down like I was. 

00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:30.840
 Or maybe I'll have a word 
 with Fatman. 

00:08:30.920 --> 00:08:36.160
 I could promise not to go to the 
 Gardaí provided that he send out... 

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:40.000
 ..a few thugs to do a job on you 
 like the one you did on me. 

00:08:40.080 --> 00:08:42.080
 Have you completely lost your mind? 

00:08:42.160 --> 00:08:44.960
 Stay away from him 
 or he'll kill us both. 

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:47.280
 I'm serious, Suzy. 

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:50.600
 I'll get even with him, 
 sooner or later. 

00:08:50.680 --> 00:08:54.120
 I just need to be careful 
 how I go about it. 

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:58.320
 I don't want you to get even. 
 I never want anything from you again.

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.560
 Don't be like that, Suzy. 

00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:07.000
 Look at this as a way 
 of bringing us close again. 

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:10.200
 I want that. Don't you? 

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:13.400
 Look what he did to you! 

00:09:17.400 --> 00:09:20.000
 Get out of my sight. 

00:09:20.080 --> 00:09:21.520
 Suzy! 

00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:23.600
 Okay, okay, I'm leaving. 

00:09:28.600 --> 00:09:31.440
 They were right 
 at the end of the day. 

00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:36.080
 I don't know how I thought 
 you could pick a child yourself. 

00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:38.160
 I suppose that can't be done. 

00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:41.240
 Any child they give you 
 will be lucky. 

00:09:41.320 --> 00:09:44.240
 You're great with kids, 
 everyone says it. 

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.600
 -Hello ladies. 
 -Peadar! 

00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:50.400
 Any chance I could leave Evan 
 with you this week? 

00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:54.160
 He said he'd love to go painting 
 with you again. 

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:58.640
 Of course, Berni. Evan is welcome 
 any time he wants to call over. 

00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:01.120
 Evainín! 

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:03.040
 Look who it is. 

00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:05.000
 Hello Evan! 

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:07.240
 -How are you? 
 -Good. 

00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:09.440
 Will you call over to Mamó tomorrow?

00:10:09.520 --> 00:10:10.680
 Yes. 

00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:15.440
 Good boy! Let's go inside and I'll 
 show you the lovely paints I have. 

00:10:16.520 --> 00:10:18.520
 Bye, Evan. 

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:20.640
 Good boy! 

00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:23.280
 -There you go, Berni. 
 -Thanks. 

00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:25.480
 Hold on a minute, Berni. 

00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:26.960
 What? 

00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:29.000
 Hear me out. 

00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:32.800
 Something is still bothering Evan. 
 I'm worried about him. 

00:10:32.880 --> 00:10:35.880
 We all know how easy it is 
 to worry you! 

00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:40.000
 When I picked him up at the naíonra,
 he was very quiet. 

00:10:40.600 --> 00:10:43.880
 He didn't even want to say goodbye 
 to the other kids. 

00:10:43.960 --> 00:10:46.800
 There's something bothering him, 
 believe me. 

00:10:46.880 --> 00:10:49.200
 There's nothing wrong with my son. 

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:51.600
 Look Berni. 

00:10:51.680 --> 00:10:55.400
 I don't mean to upset you. 
 I'm just worried about Evan. 

00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:59.040
 It's probably 
 just his wretch of a mother... 

00:10:59.120 --> 00:11:01.240
 ..who's beating him black and blue! 

00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:03.280
 That's not what I'm saying. 

00:11:03.360 --> 00:11:07.880
 Yeah right. I'll tell you 
 what the best thing for Evan is. 

00:11:07.960 --> 00:11:11.560
 For you to stay away from him 
 and mind your own business! 

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:15.240
 You have to tell the Gardaí. 

00:11:15.320 --> 00:11:17.320
 You can't let him get away with this.

00:11:17.400 --> 00:11:19.480
 I mean, look at yourself. 

00:11:19.760 --> 00:11:21.760
 Is was Daniel who did it, wasn't it?

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:24.000
 I don't want to talk about it. 

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:26.760
 You have to do something about it. 

00:11:26.840 --> 00:11:28.840
 For God's sake Suzy, he beat you. 

00:11:28.920 --> 00:11:31.160
 Knock it off, Ríona. Please. 

00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:34.920
 Things are bad enough already 
 without going to the Gardaí. 

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:37.040
 I have enough problems as it is. 

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.880
 I'll be back in a while. Okay? 

00:11:48.520 --> 00:11:50.520
 Hello! 

00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:18.840
 Thanks very much, Róise. 

00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:29.200
 Do you have the scripts 
 for those new ads, Róise? 

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:32.280
 Róise. 

00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:34.720
 I left them on your desk. 

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:38.720
 Thanks. 

00:15:43.800 --> 00:15:46.280
 Labhrás! What can I do for you? 

00:15:49.800 --> 00:15:51.880
 I've got them here. 

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:59.000
 Thank you. 

00:16:00.400 --> 00:16:03.120
 Is that the last of the information?

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:05.120
 Yes. 

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:07.320
 Good. Thank you. 

00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:11.600
 Look, I'm delighted 
 that we've put all this behind us. 

00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:17.000
 I never thought you'd allow 
 censorship like this to happen. 

00:16:17.080 --> 00:16:20.760
 It was a board decision. 
 There's nothing I can do about it. 

00:16:20.840 --> 00:16:24.720
 It was a personal decision 
 by the chairman and well you know it.

00:16:24.800 --> 00:16:28.200
 The decision has been made 
 and you should accept it. 

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:30.360
 I'm not willing to accept it. 

00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:34.600
 I want the board of directors 
 to discuss it. 

00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:40.160
 But Jason, what am I supposed 
 to tell her? 

00:16:43.560 --> 00:16:45.960
 Can't you just come and visit? 

00:16:46.040 --> 00:16:47.760
 Please. 

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:50.960
 She has no one else. 

00:16:51.520 --> 00:16:54.040
 You can't..! Jason? 

00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:58.640
 Were you in to see her? 

00:16:59.160 --> 00:17:00.960
 Yeah. 

00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:03.080
 How is she? 

00:17:03.160 --> 00:17:05.440
 Okay, I suppose. 

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:10.040
 Will the baby be okay? 

00:17:11.240 --> 00:17:13.320
 We don't know. 

00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:16.080
 The poor girl. 

00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:18.320
 Has she spoken to the Gardaí yet? 

00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:20.800
 No, she hasn't. 

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:22.600
 Why not? 

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:25.840
 Because she doesn't want 
 to tell them anything. 

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:28.480
 She's probably right. 

00:17:28.560 --> 00:17:30.880
 No, she isn't. 

00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:34.840
 Whoever did that to her 
 should pay for it. 

00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:38.400
 That's why I'm thinking 
 about going to the Gardaí. 

00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:39.640
 You? 

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:41.960
 Yeah, there's no alternative. 

00:17:44.800 --> 00:17:47.280
 I wouldn't recommend that. 

00:17:47.360 --> 00:17:49.280
 Why not? 

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:51.520
 We don't know what happened. 

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:53.760
 We didn't see anything. 

00:17:53.840 --> 00:17:56.320
 I've seen enough. Haven't you? 

00:17:57.440 --> 00:17:59.720
 I don't know about that. 

00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:03.600
 Don't tell me you don't suspect him.

00:18:04.200 --> 00:18:06.240
 Who? 

00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:08.680
 Daniel, who else? 

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.280
 Come on! 

00:18:12.360 --> 00:18:15.480
 Do you really think Daniel 
 would beat his own daughter? 

00:18:15.560 --> 00:18:17.560
 Who else would do it? 

00:18:17.640 --> 00:18:19.760
 And why else would she protect him? 

00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:25.280
 You're not one hundred per cent 
 sure about that. 

00:18:25.360 --> 00:18:29.800
 Until she makes 
 an official complaint... 

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:32.080
 ..you shouldn't go accusing anyone. 

00:18:32.160 --> 00:18:35.680
 -She could have her reasons. 
 -What do you mean? 

00:18:35.760 --> 00:18:38.800
 After all that happened 
 with Jason... 

00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:42.920
 ..there's a chance 
 that no one will believe her. 

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:46.120
 Speaking of which, 
 is Jason coming to see her? 

00:18:46.200 --> 00:18:49.320
 I only just told him 
 she's in hospital. 

00:18:49.400 --> 00:18:51.160
 And? 

00:18:51.240 --> 00:18:53.720
 And he's not interested. 

00:18:54.920 --> 00:18:59.080
 A half a ton. I'll order that now 
 and I'll ring you when it arrives. 

00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:01.360
 -Alright Micheál. 
 -Goodbye, Cóilín. 

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.440
 Come here a second. 

00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:05.760
 What did the accountant have to say?

00:19:05.840 --> 00:19:08.240
 What we expected. 

00:19:08.320 --> 00:19:11.000
 We didn't reach our targets. 

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:15.040
 If we don't make changes very soon 
 we're going to have problems. 

00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:17.120
 What can we do? 

00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:19.800
 A new advertising campaign. 

00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:22.640
 Fliers, maybe a radio ad. 

00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:25.120
 That won't work. 

00:19:25.200 --> 00:19:29.200
 We have to offer something new, 
 something no one else is providing. 

00:19:29.600 --> 00:19:31.640
 Any ideas? 

00:19:31.720 --> 00:19:34.320
 No but we have to think 
 of something quick. 

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:36.280
 We don't do enough business. 

00:19:36.360 --> 00:19:39.680
 Nor is there enough work 
 being done around here either. 

00:19:39.760 --> 00:19:43.080
 They carry out these kinds 
 of operations every day. 

00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:44.960
 Mistakes are made and people die. 

00:19:45.040 --> 00:19:47.920
 Come on Suzy. 
 Nothing is going to happen to you. 

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.520
 What does it matter? 
 I wouldn't be much of a loss anyway.

00:19:51.600 --> 00:19:54.720
 Suzy, don't say things like that. 

00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:58.800
 Why not? It would solve 
 everyone's problems if I died. 

00:19:58.880 --> 00:20:02.280
 My Dad's problems would be solved 
 as would Janet's. 

00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:06.120
 And Jason would have a clean slate 
 for the rest of his life. 

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:08.680
 That's rubbish and well you know it.

00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:11.800
 So where's Jason? 
 Why isn't he here? 

00:20:11.880 --> 00:20:13.880
 I don't know. 

00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:17.120
 He probably doesn't know 
 about this yet. 

00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:20.280
 It serves me right. 

00:20:20.360 --> 00:20:22.600
 No! No one deserves this. 

00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:27.440
 Do you know the real reason why 
 I didn't go ahead with the abortion?

00:20:27.520 --> 00:20:31.280
 Yes. Because you couldn't kill 
 that little baby. 

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.440
 I wish that were true. 

00:20:36.480 --> 00:20:39.200
 I was afraid. 

00:20:40.400 --> 00:20:44.160
 Making that decision 
 took a lot of courage, Suzy. 

00:20:44.240 --> 00:20:47.080
 Not courage but cowardice. 

00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:53.840
 I had an abortion before. 

00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:59.080
 I was well into my pregnancy 
 when it was carried out. 

00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:01.320
 There were complications. 

00:21:04.200 --> 00:21:07.880
 I backed out of the abortion 
 because I couldn't go through... 

00:21:07.960 --> 00:21:10.040
 ..with the operation. 

00:21:10.120 --> 00:21:13.880
 Now they want me to go 
 under the knife to save the baby. 

00:21:15.680 --> 00:21:20.440
 What would you do to entice customers
 who had left you to come back? 

00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:26.600
 The first thing I'd do is 
 review the company's assets. 

00:21:26.680 --> 00:21:28.680
 What are your assets? 

00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:30.840
 We're conveniently close 
 to customers. 

00:21:30.920 --> 00:21:32.920
 We know people. 

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:35.000
 What else? 

00:21:35.800 --> 00:21:39.480
 You have another asset 
 that neither of you thought of. 

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:43.200
 An asset you're not using 
 half enough. 

00:21:43.280 --> 00:21:45.320
 -What? 
 -Séamus Mhicil Tom. 

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:47.720
 Séamus! 

00:21:47.800 --> 00:21:49.800
 It's no laughing matter. 

00:21:49.880 --> 00:21:52.600
 Séamus knows everyone 
 for miles around. 

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:54.680
 He goes to the fairs. 

00:21:54.760 --> 00:21:56.840
 He knows how to get around people. 

00:21:56.920 --> 00:21:58.880
 Séamus knows how things work. 

00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:01.280
 An asset like that can't be bought. 

00:22:01.360 --> 00:22:03.320
 Gosh! 

00:22:03.400 --> 00:22:08.960
 You could send Séamus out 
 to local farmers to drum up business.

00:22:12.520 --> 00:22:17.360
 Give them a high-quality service 
 and they'll stay with you. 

00:22:18.600 --> 00:22:21.080
 You're right, Peadar. 

00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:24.840
 You could go further afield 
 for orders. 

00:22:24.920 --> 00:22:28.680
 Ciarán could easily manage 
 the store. 

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:32.240
 Fair play to you Peadar. 
 I'd never have thought of that. 

00:22:32.320 --> 00:22:34.920
 Why didn't we think of that? 

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:38.360
 There's only one problem. 

00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.080
 What? 

00:22:40.160 --> 00:22:43.720
 Séamus Mhicil Tom! 
 He's not a happy camper these days. 

00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.800
 We'll have to entice him somehow. 

00:22:46.840 --> 00:22:49.120
 That'll be your biggest obstacle. 

00:22:49.200 --> 00:22:54.000
 When Séamus gets into a mood, 
 he's as stubborn as a mule. 

00:22:54.400 --> 00:22:56.880
 Bye, Róise. 

00:22:57.600 --> 00:22:59.920
 Never mind her. 

00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:02.160
 Caitríona. 

00:23:02.240 --> 00:23:03.280
 Yeah? 

00:23:03.360 --> 00:23:06.600
 Have you told Vince yet 
 about me? 

00:23:07.600 --> 00:23:09.840
 I haven't said a word. 

00:23:09.920 --> 00:23:14.320
 Don't worry, 
 I won't mention a thing. 

00:23:16.800 --> 00:23:17.880
 Thanks. 

00:23:18.600 --> 00:23:20.600
 I'm not doing it for your sake. 

00:23:22.520 --> 00:23:25.360
 It's better for Vince 
 not to know. 

00:23:25.440 --> 00:23:29.160
 I thought he'd get back with you 
 if you told him. 

00:23:30.200 --> 00:23:32.280
 That's what he said. 

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:35.160
 But I know Vince 
 much better than that. 

00:23:35.240 --> 00:23:39.920
 Regardless of what he says, 
 he'd never forgive me or you either. 

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:44.000
 If you don't tell him, 
 you'll definitely lose him. 

00:23:50.400 --> 00:23:54.400
 Maybe this sounds strange 
 coming from me... 

00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:57.640
 ..but won't you even 
 take the chance? 

00:23:57.720 --> 00:24:00.120
 You want to get back with him, right?

00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:06.280
 Rory, if Vince found out about me 
 and you, he'd lose the head. 

00:24:06.800 --> 00:24:08.880
 You'd end up in Casualty. 

00:24:08.960 --> 00:24:11.360
 Vince would probably end up in prison

00:24:11.440 --> 00:24:13.440
 What use would that be to anyone? 

00:24:15.760 --> 00:24:18.960
 Your secret is safe with me, 
 I won't say a word. 

00:24:20.600 --> 00:24:26.000
 Róise on the other hand 
 is another matter entirely. 

00:24:26.080 --> 00:24:30.320
 I don't think they'll go to 
 the Gardaí. For another while anyway.

00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:32.400
 Why do you say that? 

00:24:32.480 --> 00:24:34.520
 I was talking to Ríona earlier. 

00:24:34.600 --> 00:24:38.560
 She's not doing anything about it. 
 She's leaving it up to Suzy. 

00:24:38.640 --> 00:24:40.520
 That's a relief. 

00:24:40.600 --> 00:24:43.600
 Is she still threatening 
 to blame me for it? 

00:24:43.680 --> 00:24:44.880
 Suzy? 

00:24:44.960 --> 00:24:46.960
 No! The Queen of England! 

00:24:47.680 --> 00:24:50.200
 Not as far as I know. 

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:53.040
 I thought you spoke to her. 

00:24:53.120 --> 00:24:56.200
 I looked in on her 
 but Ríona was there too. 

00:24:57.000 --> 00:25:00.680
 Imagine my own daughter 
 accusing me of lies like that! 

00:25:00.760 --> 00:25:03.080
 She hasn't done it so far. 

00:25:03.160 --> 00:25:05.880
 Even if she does, you'll be fine. 

00:25:08.600 --> 00:25:11.000
 Provided you didn't do it. 

00:25:11.080 --> 00:25:12.960
 Do you think I did it? 

00:25:14.200 --> 00:25:16.640
 Fatman did it. Right? 

00:25:16.720 --> 00:25:20.920
 Yes. I'll kill that bastard 
 when I get a hold of him. 

00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:22.360
 Fatman? 

00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:26.440
 I've been trying to ring him 
 but he's not answering. 

00:25:26.520 --> 00:25:30.480
 He probably doesn't want to talk 
 to you until you cool down. 

00:25:30.560 --> 00:25:34.080
 If he thinks I'll forgive him 
 he has another thing coming. 

00:25:34.160 --> 00:25:37.160
 He hurt Suzy and put 
 the baby's life in danger. 

00:25:37.240 --> 00:25:40.040
 I don't care who he is, 
 he'll pay for it. 

00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:44.160
 Do as you like but I for one 
 wouldn't draw that Fatman on me. 

00:25:44.240 --> 00:25:48.480
 He could end up killing 
 you and Suzy. He's a bad article. 

00:25:48.560 --> 00:25:51.000
 I know. I'm not that stupid. 

00:25:51.960 --> 00:25:55.680
 I'll catch up with him some day 
 when he least expects it. 

00:25:55.760 --> 00:25:58.280
 And I'll get revenge. 

00:25:58.360 --> 00:26:00.760
 Good luck with that! 

00:26:05.400 --> 00:26:07.600
 Vince hi, come in! 

00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:10.360
 I came to collect my stuff. 

00:26:16.800 --> 00:26:20.960
 Do you want a cup of tea 
 or a glass of wine maybe? 

00:26:23.440 --> 00:26:25.360
 No, thanks. 

00:26:25.440 --> 00:26:27.400
 Can't we even talk about this? 

00:26:27.480 --> 00:26:31.120
 What's the point when you won't even
 tell me what happened? 

00:26:31.200 --> 00:26:33.280
 -You know what happened. 
 -No I don't. 

00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:36.240
 Now's your chance. 
 Who were you with? 

00:26:36.320 --> 00:26:38.640
 Out with it! Who is he? 

00:26:40.800 --> 00:26:43.160
 It's your choice. I'm leaving. 

00:26:43.800 --> 00:26:46.120
 Please Vince! 

00:26:46.200 --> 00:26:47.640
 Vince! 

